1) Get the masses
2) get rid of DOS
3) edit molparam.txt so everything is in 5 columns for easy matlab reading
4) check this has been done correctly, using check_mass2X.m
5) then run convert2mass2X.m (was convert2mass20.m)
6) cp /asl/data/hitran/H2016/ISOTOPES/mass24.dat /home/sergio/SPECTRA/MASS_ISOTOPES/mass24.dat
   cp /asl/data/hitran/H2024/ISOTOPES/Readme     /home/sergio/SPECTRA/MASS_ISOTOPES/Readme_mass24

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
AIM :    Get molparams.txt and make mass24.dat, copy to /home/sergio/SPECTRA/MASS_ISOTOPES/mass24.dat
cd http://hitran.org/cia/ --> Documentation --> Isotopologues

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

1) get the masses using
     wget http://hitran.org/media/molparam.txt
   which has been saved in /asl/data/hitran/H2024/ISOTOPES


2) need to get rid of ^M in molparams.txt so either do
     dos2unix molparam.txt

or /asl/data/hitran/get_rid_of_silly_DOS.sc
  #!/bin/sh
  cat $1 | tr -d '\r' > ~/.tmp_file.txt
  mv ~/.tmp_file.txt $1

so
  cp molparam.txt molparam0.txt
  ../../get_rid_of_silly_DOS.sc molparam.txt

3) then edit molparam.txt and save it as mass24_0.dat as follows : 
   so that text is commented with % signs, and you add info to make everything 5 columns   
   so it looks like mass12.dat or mass20.dat
   In other words you are replacing
      MOL NAME       GASIID  
   with
     GASID NUMISO 0 0 0
   For example :
   
   H2O (1)
   161  9.97317E-01    1.7458E+02    1     18.010565
   181  1.99983E-03    1.7605E+02    1     20.014811
   171  3.71884E-04    1.0521E+03    6     19.014780
   162  3.10693E-04    8.6474E+02    6     19.016740
   182  6.23003E-07    8.7557E+02    6     21.020985
   172  1.15853E-07    5.2268E+03   36     20.020956
   262  2.41970E-08    1.0278E+03    1     20.022915

    becomes
    
%      H2O (1)
1 7 0 0 0
   161  9.97317E-01    1.7458E+02    1     18.010565
   181  1.99983E-03    1.7605E+02    1     20.014811
   171  3.71884E-04    1.0521E+03    6     19.014780
   162  3.10693E-04    8.6474E+02    6     19.016740
   182  6.23003E-07    8.7557E+02    6     21.020985
   172  1.15853E-07    5.2268E+03   36     20.020956
   262  2.41970E-08    1.0278E+03    1     20.022915

   first 47 lines will have the number of isotopes
     (so basically copy the first 47 lines of mass12.dat)
     (but check to make sure you get the right number of isotopes_
   then put in the masses as per molparam.txt

so that eg

>>>>>>>>>
Molecule # Iso Abundance     Q(296K)      gj    Molar Mass(g)
   H2O (1)
   161  9.97317E-01    1.7458E+02    1     18.010565
